<TITLE> Four die in Teknaf hill slide </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Teknaf, July 6 (bdnews24.com)  Four of a family died Sunday in a hill slide in Teknaf Upazila of Cox's Bazar, a police official said. A one-and-half-month-old infant, however, survived, Teknaf police officer Md Jasim Uddin said. He said the hill slide, caused by heavy downpour that started Saturday night, left four of the family dead around 1:30pm in Fakiramura area of Teknaf Sadar as huge chunks of earth came down on them. The dead are Nur Hashim Prakash Lalu, 35, his wife Madina Khatun, 22, their daughter Rehana Begum, 5, and son Redwan Ahmed, 3. Local people recovered Shahana Akhter Baishakhi, the infant, from under the mud. Teknaf Upazila Nirbahi officer Altaf Hossain Chowdhury said the incident had occurred near the BTTB office of Teknaf Sadar. People had been evacuated from the area two days ago, he added. The hill slide had killed nine people on Thursday. bdnews2
